    <id>tag:www.gov.uk,2005:PublicationesquePresenter/54874</id>
    <published>2012-07-01T01:00:00+01:00</published>
    <updated>2012-12-12T19:08:58+00:00</updated>
    <link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/continuous-improvement-strategy-and-implementation-plan-july-2012--2"/>
    <title>Continuous improvement strategy and implementation plan, July 2012  </title>
    <category>Publication</category>
    <summary>Our continuous improvement strategy describes how we are implementing 'diplomatic excellence' and how we are assessing our performance, 2011 to 2015.
</summary>
    <content type="html">&lt;div class="govspeak"&gt;&lt;p&gt;The Foreign &amp;amp; Commonwealth Office has a well established continuous improvement strategy entitled Diplomatic Excellence. It is the &lt;abbr title="Foreign &amp;amp; Commonwealth Office"&gt;FCO&lt;/abbr&gt;’s most important reform agenda for 2011 to 2015. The starting point for Diplomatic Excellence is “how can we do this better?” Our ambition is for the &lt;abbr title="Foreign &amp;amp; Commonwealth Office"&gt;FCO&lt;/abbr&gt; to be the best diplomatic service in the world. This paper describes our continuous improvement strategy and how we are implementing it. This is a living document which we will update as required.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</content>
